experience.description:
All work takes place in the Oracle ESS corporate system. Range of purchases includes goods, licenses, works and services. In subordination is department of contracts for the implementation of tender decisions.

Primary duties:
1) Taking participation in work over improvement of procurement process, implementing modifications in methodology and procurement procedure;
2) Conducting tenders and/or purchases from a single source on both the local and global markets in accordance with the company's internal regulations and the responsibility distribution matrix namely:

- Analysis of technical specification given by the customer for correctness and compliance with the procurement procedure;
- Projects kick-off to the Procurement Committee consisting of the company’s top-management
- Elaborating strategic schemes for tenders and conducting the RFI procedure as needed;
-  Approval the following: tender expert group, format of the tender, blocking factors, list of requirements, evaluation matrix, TCO-model/NPV, RFP package, schedule of conduction of the  tender. All these docs approve at the Tender commission;
- Sending out approved docs and further receipt bids and other filled documentation from participants;
- Offers analysis in conjunction with the Expert group and preparation of the presentation containing results of the 1-st stage;
-  Conducting the 2-nd stage in form of: a) online auction; b) request for brighten priced offers;
- Preparation of the detailed protocol and presentation for the Tender commission;
- Detailed coverage of the tender at the Procurement committee and its subsequent approval;
- Trasmission of the approved decision to the contract dept. for the contract execution.
- Regular meetings with the Dutch headquarter in order to discuss the status of projects and the development strategy for subsequent periods.

Secondary duties:
1) Approval of contracts in the Oracle ESS ERP;
2) Receipt of the ready-made solutions from Veon’s HQ and passing to the contract dept. for the further contracting;
3) Cross-functional interaction by means of meetings with the aim of solving different kind of issues;
6) Trainings participation and continuous skill improvement.

In the list of companies with whom commercial relations has been established all well-known global brands, such as Microsoft, Micro Focus, Thales DIS, Oracle, Kaspersky Lab, Amdocs, Huawei, ZTE, Opencode Limited and others.

Preparation of the project budget (in the direction of the "main equipment") and purchasing Viessmann, Caterpillar, Wilson, Genebre, Willo, RAZ, APROVIS, Guntner, Weishaupt equipment in foreign countries (boilers, burners, gensets, pipeline fittings, etc.) ELCO Burners, Ecoflam and others.;

Searching for equipment and suppliers abroad (Europe, China);

Translation of technical documentation for the block-modular boiler house to provide foreign general contractor “Gazprom pererabotka Blagoveshchensk” LLC (within the framework of the Amursky GPZ project) into English;

Picking construction sites with all necessary equipment in accordance with the engineer-designer's data;

Drafting and approval of contracts with counterparties;

Control of payments under contracts;

Calculation of logistics and customs payments;

Documents preparation and its submission to customs;

Warehouse inventory control.

All realized projects indicated on the company's website.

Marketing researches of the IT equipment market for business automation in retail using many analytic methods;

Time series analysis and correlation-regression analysis to investigate the relationship and tightness between demand on products and time period / elasticity of one and the other product / consumer demand and market supply;

Searching and analysis of the IT product suppliers (monoblocks, data collection terminals, cash register equipment, monitors, printers, price-checkers, scanners, software and much more);

Negotiations and conclusion of international contracts. During the working period I executed about 100 contracts for supply;

Market prices monitoring;

Searching for opportunities in order to gain discounts and special prices from suppliers;

Participation in the calculation of full self-cost;

Participation in the purchases budgeting;

Tracing the supply chain and working with shipping documents (CCD, CMR, etc.);

Control payment terms for the delivered goods, developing a mechanism to optimize purchases and participating in pricing of products in accordance with company regulations;

The main customers were such companies as X5 Retail Group, Magnit, Technosila, Leroy Merlin, Sportmaster, Auchan and others;

Conducting a project to equip industrial equipment with special reading chips from the ground up and until the equipment registered by the state bodies of the Russian Federation in accordance with the 54-FL. The total cost of purchased equipment for this project is 50 million rubles;

Major suppliers were such as Wincor Nixdorf, Wavelink, DIGI, Anritsu, Toshiba, Oracle, Datalogic, Mobile Compia, Sewoo, Toyota, Dell and others. 

During my work many projects for the purchase and equipping of production areas of leading retail market players with industrial equipment and software have been implemented. Main achievement is replacement of expensive and not popular commodities in favor of cheaper substitute goods without loss of quality. This led to the self-cost and logistic costs reduction, allowed to increase market share, balance Net Working Capital and provide larger proportions of won tenders.

Business correspondence with counterparts;

Composition and conclusion of international contracts on delivery of high-tech heat-shrinkable insulation materials for full range of pipelines in oil&gas and housing sector;

Formation and implementation of sales schedule, marketing researches, participation in budget formation of FEA Dept.;

Cooperation with agents in foreign countries;

Calculation of required products, formation and submission technical and commercial offers to clients (participation in tenders);

Participation in the calculation of full self-cost;

Translation and understanding technical documentation of projects;

Preparing shipping documents for custom clearance (mill test certificates, certificates of origin, invoices, packing lists, bills of lading, CMR, currency transaction report forms, remittance orders. Provisioning financial reports to shareholders;

Shipments in accordance with INCOTERMS-2010 to Egypt, Turkey, Brazil, Bulgaria, Iran, China, Myanmar and other countries;

Full legal arrangements including documents legalization in embassies;

Cooperation with carrier (tracking of delivery), insurance company, various international logistic organizations, certification authorities (Moscow Chamber of Commerce and Industry, Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation), collaboration with Federal Customs Service in order to confirm goods exportation outside the Russian Federation (VAT refund);

Signing additional agreements with counterparties, composition and signing lists of disagreements, acts of reconciliations;

Closing receivables for the goods delivered, interaction with the Issuer on subject of payment under a letter of credit and with the Payee on subject of collection of payments;

Handling complaints;

Sending samples to Bodycote (UK), Gas Technology Institute, Partech (both - USA), DVGW (Germany), participating international seminars;

Participating exhibitions (Annual Pipeline Coating Exhibition) and conferences (Corrosion Protection Conference), business trips to objects of pipeline construction works, advising (in conjunction with technical specialist) on application and operation of the product;

Work with re-importation of goods from consumer countries;

Among the achievements I would like to emphasize my direct participation in establishment of commercial relations with such companies as Petrojet, GASCO (both - Egypt), Betta Contech (Bulgaria), SINOPEC, CNPC (both - China), Yalcin Boru (Turkey), Petrobras, NIOC (Iran), Lukoil Middle East (UAE).
